cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.GR, cs.IR 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as image matching and geolocalization, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The use of deep CNN architectures and loss functions for cross-domain matching suggests a focus on machine learning and artificial intelligence, which are covered by cs.AI and cs.LG. The paper also explores mechanisms for matching despite unknown orientation, which could fall under the category of graphics (cs.GR) or information retrieval (cs.IR).
